    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "In e75f5d216cc94cf2bd953c99960786ab0a83daff and c9dcdb4b73dc26ed72d0e3401f393d1c130fe6ea I simplified the flow and the DX.\r\n\r\nThere's now a single option: `getLocation`. We don't need to abstract `window.history.pushState` because `router.write` doesn't happen on the server. We can guard `router.write` with an environment check.\r\n\r\n`getLocation` was updated to throw early when it detects that `window` is not defined. The error message explains that you need to provide `getLocation` in environments where `window` doesn't exist.\r\n\r\nLmk what you think.",
